        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 11:41AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1141 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Patroon, or 19 miles southeast of Center, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Converse, Oak Grove, Huxley, Noble, Toledo Bend Reservoir North
and Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
